reviews.review_text:
Really Fine Job!!! Understanding the issues witth getting this recording at all, and having heard a LOT of other AUD tapes from this show/run, this SHINES! Seperation is about perfect. Full, "outdoors" openness to it, without sounding like it was recorded using a needle and a roll of paper.  Would love to hear this matrixed with Charlie Miller's SBD tape, here: https://archive.org/details/gd93-01-26.sbd.miller.26346.sbeok.shnf

.. would be almost perfect. Though the SBD recording a bit over-driven in the vocals particularly, it's still pretty fine. 
I always loved the Dead best when they let songs and setlists breathe, and relax like this. Especially on a warm summer night at Pine Knob or Deer Creek, Alpine... yeah.
